description.narrative: IR3 on EPI: By 2015, immunization inequities (in particular on hepatitis B, polio and measles,) are reduced, and intervention coverage is improved in vulnerable groups through increasingly standardized and evidence-based immunization policies, C4D approaches, routine service delivery and M&E., which contributes to Child Health, Health â€“ General, Immunization, Polio Eradication, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2015, children and women in China, particularly the poor and vulnerable, will enjoy a better health and nutrition status, and protection from impoverishment due to ill health.
